<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <%- include('partials/head'); %>
    <link href="css/styles.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body id="page-top">
    <%- include('partials/navbar'); %>
    <section id="contest" class="my-5">
        <div class="container px-5">
            <div class="row gx-5 justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-lg-8">
                    <img src="assets/img/contest/contest_header.png" class="img-fluid mb-4" alt="Contest Header Image">
                    <h2 class="font-alt">Mini-Map Radar Theme Contest</h2>
                    <p class="lead">Prize Fund: $100 + a percentage from theme sales to the winners</p>
                    <p class="lead">Deadline: September 1</p>
                    <h3 class="mt-4">Contest Details</h3>
                    <p>We are excited to announce the Mini-Map Radar Theme Contest! This is your chance to showcase your creativity and design skills by creating an original theme for the Mini-Map Radar app. The winning entries will not only receive a cash prize but also a percentage of the sales from their theme.</p>
                    
                    <h4 class="mt-4">Conditions</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Create an Original Theme:</strong> Come up with an innovative and cool theme for the Mini-Map Radar app.</li>
                        <li><strong>Prepare Concept Screens:</strong> Design concept screens that illustrate your theme.</li>
                        <li><strong>Submit Your Work:</strong> Package your submission in a zip archive and send it to <a href="mailto:dev@mini-map.app">dev@mini-map.app</a> by June 19.</li>
                        <li><strong>Win and Get Rewarded:</strong> Find out if you're a winner and enjoy the prizes and recognition!</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="mt-4">Requirements</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Main Screen:</strong> Design a visually appealing and functional main screen.</li>
                        <li><strong>10 Vector Icons:</strong> Create 10 unique vector icons that complement your theme.</li>
                        <li><strong>AR Mode Concept:</strong> Provide a concept for the AR mode on the phone, which should include:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mini-map</li>
                                <li>Street name</li>
                                <li>Notification</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Additional Screens:</strong> Include designs for training, time, and weather screens.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="mt-4">Limitations</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Device Sizes:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>368x448</li>
                                <li>324x394</li>
                                <li>396x484</li>
                                <li>352x430</li>
                                <li>410x502</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Color Restrictions:</strong> You cannot change the color of specific map elements; only the overall color can be adjusted. However, the map frame can be customized without limitations.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="mt-4">Judging Criteria</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Originality (35%):</strong> How unique and innovative is the theme? Does it offer a fresh perspective or a creative approach?</li>
                        <li><strong>Usability (30%):</strong> How easy is it to navigate and use the theme? Is the interface intuitive and user-friendly?</li>
                        <li><strong>Aesthetics (25%):</strong> How visually appealing is the theme? Does it have a cohesive design that enhances the user experience?</li>
                        <li><strong>Relevance (10%):</strong> How well does the theme align with the overall purpose of the Mini-Map Radar app? Does it add value to the user experience?</li>
                    </ul>
                    <img src="assets/img/contest/contest_preview.png" class="img-fluid mb-4" alt="Contest Examples">
                    <p class="text-center mb-4">Explore some examples and get inspired for the Mini-Map Radar Theme Contest.</p>
                    <h4 class="mt-4">Submission Format</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>File Type:</strong> All submissions must be in a zip archive format.</li>
                        <li><strong>Naming Convention:</strong> The zip archive should be named as follows: YourName_ThemeName.zip</li>
                        <li><strong>Included Files:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Concept Screens:</strong> PNG or JPEG images of the main screen, AR mode concepts, and any additional screens (training, time, weather).</li>
                                <li><strong>Vector Icons:</strong> SVG files for the 10 required icons.</li>
                                <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> A PDF document that includes:
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>A brief description of the theme.</li>
                                        <li>Instructions on how to implement the theme within the Mini-Map Radar app.</li>
                                        <li>Any additional notes or explanations that might help the judges understand your design choices.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Submission:</strong> Send the zip archive to <a href="mailto:dev@mini-map.app">dev@mini-map.app</a> by the deadline of June 19.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="mt-4">Prizes</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>First Place:</strong> $50</li>
                        <li><strong>Second Place:</strong> $25</li>
                        <li><strong>Third Place:</strong> $25</li>
                        <li>In addition to the cash prizes, winners will also receive a percentage of the sales from their theme.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="mt-4">Legal Terms</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Ownership and Rights:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>By submitting an entry, you confirm that the design is your original work and does not infringe on any third-party rights.</li>
                                <li>You retain the copyright to your submitted design. However, by entering the contest, you grant Mini-Map Radar a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, reproduce, and distribute your design for promotional and commercial purposes.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Use of Entries:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mini-Map Radar reserves the right to modify or adapt the submitted designs as necessary to fit the app's requirements.</li>
                                <li>The winning designs may be used in the Mini-Map Radar app and associated marketing materials.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> All personal information collected from participants will be used solely for the purposes of the contest and will not be shared with third parties without your consent.</li>
                        <li><strong>Disqualification:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Entries that do not adhere to the submission guidelines or contain inappropriate content will be disqualified.</li>
                                <li>Any form of intellectual property theft will result in immediate disqualification.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Contest Changes:</strong> Mini-Map Radar reserves the right to make changes to the contest rules or cancel the contest at any time. Any changes will be communicated to participants promptly.</li>
                        <li><strong>Acceptance:</strong> By submitting an entry, you agree to all the terms and conditions outlined above.</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p class="mt-4">Get creative and start designing your theme today! We can't wait to see what you come up with. Good luck!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <%- include('partials/footer'); %>
</body>
</html>
